
[1]hyperbate

   HY'PERBATE, n. [Gr. to transgress, or go beyond.

   In grammar, a figurative construction, inverting the natural and proper
   order of words and sentences. The species are the anastrophe,the
   hysteron proteron, the hypallage, the synchysis, the tmesis, the
   parenthesis, and the proper hyperbaton, which last is a long retention
   of the verb which completes the sentence.
